Digital CommunicationsAssociates Inc said it agreed with Fox Technology Inc &lt;FOXT.O>to buy its Fox Research Inc unit for a cash payment and theassumption of liabilities of around 10 mln dlrs.    The company said part of the agreement includes payment ofup to an additional 6.5 mln dlrs based on the performance ofthe unit in the year following the closing.    The company said the deal is expected to be closed inmid-August.    Fox Research develops, makes and markets local areanetworks for personal computers. Reuter&#3;